244
00:16:09.800 --> 00:16:12.189
This is Deputy Chief Dwayne Robinson.

245
00:16:12.280 --> 00:16:13.156
Who is this?

246
00:16:13.240 --> 00:16:15.231
This is Hans Gruber.

247
00:16:15.920 --> 00:16:19.276
I assume you realise the futility
of direct action against me.

248
00:16:19.360 --> 00:16:21.191
We have no wish for further loss of life.

249
00:16:21.280 --> 00:16:24.192
What is it you do wish for?

250
00:16:24.280 --> 00:16:28.353
I have comrades in arms
around the world languishing in prison.

251
00:16:28.440 --> 00:16:31.989
The American State Department
enjoys rattling its sabre for its own ends.

252
00:16:32.080 --> 00:16:34.036
Now it can rattle it for me.

253
00:16:35.400 --> 00:16:39.393
The following people
are to be released from their captors.

254
00:16:39.480 --> 00:16:42.472
In Northern Ireland.
seven members of the New Provo Front.

255
00:16:42.560 --> 00:16:46.997
<i>In Canada. the five imprisoned leaders</i>
<i>of Liberté de Quebec.</i>

256
00:16:47.080 --> 00:16:50.868
<i>In Sri Lanka. the nine members</i>
<i>of the Asian Dawn.</i>

257
00:16:50.960 --> 00:16:52.393
What the fuck?

258
00:16:52.480 --> 00:16:54.232
<i>(whispers)</i> Asian Dawn?

259
00:16:54.320 --> 00:16:56.709
I read about them in <i>Time</i> magazine.

260
00:16:56.800 --> 00:17:00.554
When these revolutionary
brothers and sisters are free...

261
00:17:00.640 --> 00:17:03.712
...the hostages in this building
will be taken to the roof...

262
00:17:03.800 --> 00:17:08.271
...and they will accompany us in helicopters
to LA International Airport...

263
00:17:08.360 --> 00:17:12.751
...where they will be given further
instructions. You have two hours to comply.

264
00:17:12.840 --> 00:17:16.150
Wait a minute. Uh. Mr. Gruber. This is crazy.

265
00:17:16.240 --> 00:17:19.835
I don't have the authority.
Two hours is not enough.

266
00:17:19.920 --> 00:17:22.115
Hello? Hello!

267
00:17:24.120 --> 00:17:27.157
Did you get all that?
We got to make some calls.

268
00:17:27.240 --> 00:17:29.276
Do you think they'll even try?

269
00:17:29.360 --> 00:17:30.998
Who cares?

270
00:17:33.600 --> 00:17:35.670
Theo. are we on schedule?

271
00:17:35.760 --> 00:17:37.637
One more to go. then it's up to you.

272
00:17:37.720 --> 00:17:40.996
You better be right.
because the last one will take a miracle.

273
00:17:41.080 --> 00:17:42.559
It's Christmas. Theo.

274
00:17:42.640 --> 00:17:45.074
It's the time of miracles.
so be of good cheer...

275
00:17:45.160 --> 00:17:47.833
...and call me when you hit the last lock.

276
00:17:48.520 --> 00:17:49.509
Karl...

277
00:17:49.600 --> 00:17:53.115
...hunt that little shit down
and get those detonators.

278
00:17:53.200 --> 00:17:55.236
Fritz is checking the explosives.

279
00:17:55.320 --> 00:17:57.880
I'll check the explosives.
You just get the detonators.

280
00:17:58.800 --> 00:18:00.199
Hey. Powell. you out there?

281
00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:03.278
I'm here. John. I'm here.

282
00:18:03.360 --> 00:18:06.716
You gotta believe me.
There was nothing I could do.

283
00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:10.639
Well. it's gonna be
both our asses if you're wrong.

284
00:18:10.720 --> 00:18:12.199
I hear you.

285
00:18:17.880 --> 00:18:20.189
Did you catch that bullshit
Hans was running?

286
00:18:20.280 --> 00:18:22.714
<i>It doesn't make sense. man.</i>

287
00:18:24.000 --> 00:18:27.834
Don't ask me. I'm just a deskjockey
who was on my way home when you rang.

288
00:18:27.920 --> 00:18:31.390
The way you drove that car.
I figured you for the street. Al.

289
00:18:31.480 --> 00:18:34.313
<i>In my youth. In my youth.</i>

290
00:18:34.520 --> 00:18:39.389
<i>... author of "Hostage Terrorist.</i>
<i>Terrorist Hostage: A Study in Duality."</i>

291
00:18:39.480 --> 00:18:42.870
<i>Dr Hasseldorf. what can we expect</i>
<i>in the next few hours?</i>

292
00:18:42.960 --> 00:18:43.676
<i>Well. Gail...</i>

293
00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:48.515
...the hostages should be going through
the early stages of the Helsinki Syndrome.

294
00:18:48.600 --> 00:18:50.352
As in Helsinki. Sweden.

295
00:18:50.440 --> 00:18:51.953
<i>(Hasseldorf)</i> Finland.

296
00:18:52.040 --> 00:18:55.510
Basically. it's when the hostages
and the terrorists...

297
00:18:55.600 --> 00:19:00.230
...go through a psychological transference
and a projection of dependency.

298
00:19:00.320 --> 00:19:03.039
<i>A strange sort of trust and bond develops.</i>

299
00:19:03.120 --> 00:19:07.910
<i>We've had situations where the hostages</i>
<i>have embraced their captors after release...</i>

300
00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:10.230
<i>... and even corresponded with them in prison.</i>

301
00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:13.113
No. no. darling. Asian Dawn. Dawn.

302
00:19:13.200 --> 00:19:16.033
D-A-W-N.

303
00:19:16.120 --> 00:19:17.519
Sir?
- Yeah?

304
00:19:17.600 --> 00:19:19.431
Sir. the FBI is here.

305
00:19:19.520 --> 00:19:23.149
The FBI is here now?
- Yes. sir. Right over there.

306
00:19:23.240 --> 00:19:24.309
Hold this.

307
00:19:24.600 --> 00:19:26.750
Want a breath mint?

308
00:19:30.640 --> 00:19:32.471
<i>(Robinson)</i> How you doin'. man?

309
00:19:33.000 --> 00:19:35.514
I'm Agent Johnson.
This is Special Agent Johnson.

310
00:19:35.600 --> 00:19:38.797
Oh. how you doing?
- No relation.

311
00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:40.154
I'm. uh...

312
00:19:41.520 --> 00:19:45.195
I'm Dwayne Robinson. LAPD.
I'm in charge here.

313
00:19:45.280 --> 00:19:47.236
Not any more.

314
00:20:39.720 --> 00:20:43.110
Hi. there. How you doing?

315
00:20:46.320 --> 00:20:47.309
Ohh...

316
00:20:48.840 --> 00:20:51.877
Please. God. No.
You're one of them. aren't you?

317
00:20:51.960 --> 00:20:53.439
You're one of them.

318
00:20:53.520 --> 00:20:56.273
No! Don't kill me! Please!

319
00:20:56.360 --> 00:20:58.715
Don't kill me. please! Please. please!

320
00:20:58.800 --> 00:21:01.473
Whoa. Relax. I'm not gonna hurt you.

321
00:21:01.560 --> 00:21:03.152
I'm not gonna hurt you!

322
00:21:05.600 --> 00:21:07.158
Oh. God.

323
00:21:10.480 --> 00:21:13.552
What are you doin' up here?
What were you lookin' for?

324
00:21:13.640 --> 00:21:15.949
I managed to get out of there and...

325
00:21:16.040 --> 00:21:19.032
...I was just trying to get up on the roof...

326
00:21:19.120 --> 00:21:21.714
...and see if I could signal for help.

327
00:21:23.160 --> 00:21:25.196
It's through here. Come and help.

328
00:21:25.280 --> 00:21:28.272
Hold it. Forget the roof.

329
00:21:28.960 --> 00:21:31.679
Forget the roof. They got people all over it.

330
00:21:33.040 --> 00:21:35.349
You wanna stay alive. you stay with me.

331
00:21:38.120 --> 00:21:40.076
The best we can figure it...

332
00:21:40.160 --> 00:21:43.516
...we've got maybe
30 or 35 hostages up there...

333
00:21:43.600 --> 00:21:45.431
...probably on the 30th floor...

334
00:21:45.520 --> 00:21:48.990
...and maybe seven or eight
terrorists up there.

335
00:21:49.080 --> 00:21:51.150
Sounds like an A-7 scenario.

336
00:21:51.240 --> 00:21:53.549
Thank you. We'll handle it from here.

337
00:21:53.640 --> 00:21:56.359
When we commandeer your men.
we'll try and let you know.

338
00:21:56.440 --> 00:21:58.317
Aren't you forgetting something?

339
00:21:58.400 --> 00:21:59.355
Such as?

340
00:21:59.440 --> 00:22:01.032
What about John McClane?

341
00:22:01.120 --> 00:22:04.112
He's the reason we have any information.

342
00:22:04.200 --> 00:22:07.670
He's also the reason
you're facing seven terrorists. not twelve.

343
00:22:07.760 --> 00:22:09.990
He's inside? Who is he?

344
00:22:10.080 --> 00:22:12.878
He might be a cop. We're checking on that.

345
00:22:12.960 --> 00:22:15.520
One of yours?
- No. no way.

346
00:22:20.840 --> 00:22:21.670
You smoke?

347
00:22:23.160 --> 00:22:24.593
Yeah.

348
00:22:29.120 --> 00:22:30.269
Thanks.

349
00:22:34.000 --> 00:22:36.753
You don't work for Nakatomi.

350
00:22:40.880 --> 00:22:43.633
And if you're not one of them...

351
00:22:45.640 --> 00:22:47.995
I'm a cop from New York.

352
00:22:48.840 --> 00:22:50.353
New York?

353
00:22:50.440 --> 00:22:51.475
Yeah.

354
00:22:52.360 --> 00:22:55.079
Got invited to
the Christmas party by mistake.

355
00:22:55.160 --> 00:22:56.388
Who knew?

356
00:23:04.640 --> 00:23:08.519
Better than being caught
with your pants down. huh?

357
00:23:15.560 --> 00:23:16.959
I'm John McClane.

358
00:23:18.240 --> 00:23:19.673
You're. uh...

359
00:23:21.000 --> 00:23:22.069
Clay.

360
00:23:24.480 --> 00:23:25.754
Bill Clay.

361
00:23:31.640 --> 00:23:33.631
Know how to use a handgun. Bill?

362
00:23:35.000 --> 00:23:39.152
I spent a weekend at a combat ranch.
That game with the guns that shoot red paint.

363
00:23:39.240 --> 00:23:41.390
Probably seems stupid to you.

364
00:23:42.760 --> 00:23:43.909
Nope.

365
00:23:46.880 --> 00:23:48.632
Time for the real thing. Bill.

366
00:23:56.840 --> 00:23:59.593
All you got to do is pull the trigger.

367
00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:00.237
Come on.

368
00:24:08.240 --> 00:24:09.992
<i>33. Stockwerk. Kommt sofort.</i>

369
00:24:12.520 --> 00:24:13.589
<i>(click)</i>

370
00:24:18.880 --> 00:24:22.998
Put down the gun
and give me my detonators.

371
00:24:27.240 --> 00:24:28.593
Well. well. well...

372
00:24:30.480 --> 00:24:31.469
Hans.

373
00:24:32.480 --> 00:24:34.914
Put it down now.

374
00:24:38.360 --> 00:24:41.716
That's pretty tricky with that accent.

375
00:24:41.800 --> 00:24:44.872
You oughta be on fuckin' TV with that accent.

376
00:24:47.080 --> 00:24:50.550
But what do you want with the detonators?

377
00:24:50.640 --> 00:24:53.200
I already used all the explosives.

378
00:24:55.440 --> 00:24:56.714
Or did I?

379
00:24:58.120 --> 00:24:59.678
I'm going to count to three.

380
00:24:59.760 --> 00:25:02.069
Yeah. Like you did with Takagi?

381
00:25:02.160 --> 00:25:03.070
<i>(click)</i>

382
00:25:03.160 --> 00:25:03.797
Oops.

383
00:25:03.880 --> 00:25:05.552
<i>(clicking)</i>

384
00:25:05.640 --> 00:25:06.914
No bullets.

385
00:25:07.000 --> 00:25:09.958
What do you think...
I'm fucking stupid. Hans?

386
00:25:10.040 --> 00:25:11.075
You were saying?

387
00:26:03.520 --> 00:26:03.997
Karl.

388
00:26:04.920 --> 00:26:06.911
<i>Schieß auf das Fenster.</i>

389
00:26:13.360 --> 00:26:15.191
Shoot the glass!

390
00:26:47.200 --> 00:26:48.633
Jesus Christ!

391
00:27:16.680 --> 00:27:19.513
Smile. Karl. We're back in business.

392
00:27:22.080 --> 00:27:24.958
<i>... is the last resort of diplomacy...</i>

393
00:27:25.040 --> 00:27:30.831
<i>... then couldn't we say that terrorism</i>
<i>has an equal claim on being that. too?</i>

394
00:27:31.520 --> 00:27:33.556
Tell me you got something.

395
00:27:33.640 --> 00:27:37.428
McClane's name. badge number.
employment record. vital statistics...

396
00:27:37.520 --> 00:27:39.909
...and his family's home address...

397
00:27:40.000 --> 00:27:41.353
...right here in LA.

398
00:27:43.160 --> 00:27:43.876
Whoo!

399
00:27:44.680 --> 00:27:46.671
<i>(elevator bell)</i>

400
00:27:49.240 --> 00:27:50.355
Go to work.

401
00:27:50.560 --> 00:27:52.278
Got it.

402
00:28:03.920 --> 00:28:07.037
God. that man looks really pissed.

403
00:28:09.280 --> 00:28:11.191
He's still alive.

404
00:28:11.560 --> 00:28:12.549
What?

405
00:28:20.960 --> 00:28:22.598
<i>(groans)</i>

406
00:28:32.840 --> 00:28:36.958
Hans. heat up that miracle because
we just broke through on number six...

407
00:28:37.040 --> 00:28:39.634
...and the electromagnetic
came down like an anvil.

408
00:28:39.720 --> 00:28:44.840
Have a look at what our friends
outside are doing and I'll be right up.

409
00:28:47.160 --> 00:28:48.275
<i>(Powell) Hey. John.</i>

410
00:28:48.360 --> 00:28:50.669
<i>John McClane. you still with us?</i>

411
00:28:50.760 --> 00:28:51.829
Yeah.

412
00:28:52.600 --> 00:28:56.275
But all things being equal.
I'd rather be in Philadelphia.

413
00:28:56.840 --> 00:28:58.876
Chalk up two more bad guys.

414
00:28:59.200 --> 00:29:02.158
<i>The boys down here will be glad to hear that.</i>

415
00:29:02.720 --> 00:29:04.517
<i>We got a pool going on you.</i>

416
00:29:04.600 --> 00:29:06.397
What kind of odds am I getting?

417
00:29:06.480 --> 00:29:08.072
<i>You don't want to know.</i>

418
00:29:08.160 --> 00:29:09.513
Put me down for 20.

419
00:29:09.600 --> 00:29:10.715
I'm good for it.

420
00:29:14.480 --> 00:29:17.040
<i>Hey. pal. you got flat feet?</i>

421
00:29:19.440 --> 00:29:21.556
What the hell you talking about. man?

422
00:29:21.640 --> 00:29:23.949
Something had to get you off the street.

423
00:29:24.040 --> 00:29:25.189
<i>What's the matter?</i>

424
00:29:25.280 --> 00:29:28.397
<i>You don't think a desk job</i>
<i>is a noble effort for a cop?</i>

425
00:29:30.240 --> 00:29:31.434
<i>No.</i>

426
00:29:34.760 --> 00:29:36.716
I had an accident.

427
00:29:36.800 --> 00:29:38.995
<i>The way you drive. I can see why.</i>

428
00:29:39.080 --> 00:29:39.796
<i>What'd you do?</i>

429
00:29:39.880 --> 00:29:42.348
Run over your captain's foot with the car?

430
00:29:46.080 --> 00:29:47.229
I shot a kid.

431
00:29:48.760 --> 00:29:50.512
<i>He was 13 years old.</i>

432
00:29:51.720 --> 00:29:55.599
<i>It was dark. I couldn't see him.</i>
<i>He had a ray gun. looked real enough.</i>

433
00:29:58.720 --> 00:30:02.315
When you're a rookie. they teach you
everything about being a cop...

434
00:30:02.400 --> 00:30:04.197
...except how to live with a mistake.

435
00:30:08.040 --> 00:30:12.636
<i>Anyway. I just couldn't bring myself</i>
<i>to draw my gun on anybody again.</i>

436
00:30:15.560 --> 00:30:16.834
<i>Sorry. man.</i>

437
00:30:18.280 --> 00:30:20.874
Hey. man. how could you know?

438
00:30:23.120 --> 00:30:24.872
I feel like shit anyway.

439
00:30:27.840 --> 00:30:29.353
Well. this won't matter.

440
00:30:29.440 --> 00:30:33.991
The LAPD is not calling the shots
down here any more.

441
00:30:36.360 --> 00:30:37.475
The Feds?

442
00:30:38.000 --> 00:30:39.035
You got it.

443
00:33:33.400 --> 00:33:35.231
<i>(Theo)</i> It's gonna go. It's gonna go!

444
00:33:35.320 --> 00:33:36.548
<i>(lock releases)</i>

445
00:33:36.960 --> 00:33:38.313
Yes!

446
00:33:38.400 --> 00:33:39.992
<i>(buzzers)</i>

447
00:33:52.680 --> 00:33:53.908
<i>(buzzers stop)</i>

448
00:34:00.240 --> 00:34:02.231
Merry Christmas.

449
00:34:03.120 --> 00:34:06.157
They must be pissing in their pants.

450
00:34:06.240 --> 00:34:08.037
The mayor is gonna have my ass.

451
00:34:14.760 --> 00:34:16.034
Whoo!

452
00:34:28.480 --> 00:34:30.630
What are we gonna do now?

453
00:34:30.720 --> 00:34:33.598
Arrest them for not paying their electric bill?

454
00:34:33.680 --> 00:34:35.398
We've shut them down.

455
00:34:35.480 --> 00:34:38.756
We let them sweat for a while.
then give them helicopters.

456
00:34:38.840 --> 00:34:40.956
Right up the ass.

457
00:34:43.440 --> 00:34:44.919
This is Agent Johnson.

458
00:34:45.000 --> 00:34:46.319
No. the other one.

459
00:34:46.400 --> 00:34:49.551
I want air support
ready to lift off in five minutes.

460
00:34:49.640 --> 00:34:52.950
Damn right. Fully armed. We're on the way.

461
00:34:58.640 --> 00:35:00.471
Oh. yes!

462
00:35:02.120 --> 00:35:04.429
I wish to talk to the FBI.

463
00:35:06.920 --> 00:35:08.956
This is Special Agent Johnson.

464
00:35:09.040 --> 00:35:13.318
<i>The State Department has arranged</i>
<i>for the return of your comrades.</i>

465
00:35:13.400 --> 00:35:15.914
Helicopters are en route as you requested.

466
00:35:16.000 --> 00:35:18.150
<i>I hear you. We'll be ready.</i>

467
00:35:18.240 --> 00:35:20.549
When he figures out
what hit him. he'll be in a body bag.

468
00:35:21.360 --> 00:35:24.113
When they touch down. we'll blow the roof.

469
00:35:34.960 --> 00:35:36.393
Ah! Jeez!

470
00:35:36.480 --> 00:35:37.469
Powell?

471
00:35:38.280 --> 00:35:40.032
Yo. Powell. you got a minute?

472
00:35:41.720 --> 00:35:43.358
I'm here. John.

473
00:35:45.000 --> 00:35:48.390
Listen. I'm starting
to get a bad feeling up here.

474
00:35:48.480 --> 00:35:50.357
I want you to do something for me.

475
00:35:50.440 --> 00:35:51.634
Um...

476
00:35:53.120 --> 00:35:56.874
I want you to find my wife.
Don't ask me how. By then you'll know how.

477
00:35:56.960 --> 00:36:03.354
Uh. I want you to tell her something.
I want you to tell her that...

478
00:36:04.200 --> 00:36:04.837
...um...

479
00:36:10.000 --> 00:36:12.560
Tell her it took me a while to figure out...

480
00:36:12.640 --> 00:36:14.631
...what ajerk I've been...

481
00:36:15.200 --> 00:36:16.394
...but. um...

482
00:36:18.000 --> 00:36:18.955
...that...

483
00:36:22.680 --> 00:36:25.274
...that when things started to pan out for her...

484
00:36:25.360 --> 00:36:29.239
...I shoulda been more supportive.

485
00:36:29.680 --> 00:36:30.510
And. uh...

486
00:36:31.960 --> 00:36:34.997
<i>... I just should have been behind her more.</i>

487
00:36:37.440 --> 00:36:38.634
Oh. shit.

488
00:36:41.200 --> 00:36:43.191
Tell her that. um...

489
00:36:44.080 --> 00:36:48.471
...that she's the best thing
that ever happened to a bum like me.

490
00:36:50.320 --> 00:36:53.630
She's heard me say "I love you"
a thousand times.

491
00:36:54.760 --> 00:36:58.036
She never heard me say "I'm sorry".

492
00:36:58.640 --> 00:37:04.590
I want you to tell her that. Al.
Tell her that John said that he was sorry.

493
00:37:05.920 --> 00:37:06.909
OK?

494
00:37:07.840 --> 00:37:08.955
You got that. man?

495
00:37:09.040 --> 00:37:11.235
<i>Yeah. I got it. John.</i>

496
00:37:12.480 --> 00:37:14.869
But you can tell her that yourself.

497
00:37:15.280 --> 00:37:19.193
You just watch your ass
and you'll make it out. You hear me?

498
00:37:19.280 --> 00:37:21.555
<i>I guess that's up to the man upstairs.</i>

499
00:37:24.800 --> 00:37:26.233
<i>John?</i>

500
00:37:27.040 --> 00:37:28.439
<i>John?</i>

501
00:37:28.880 --> 00:37:32.270
What the fuck
were you doing upstairs. Hans?

502
00:37:33.840 --> 00:37:34.829
<i>John?</i>

503
00:37:34.920 --> 00:37:37.912
No. Al. listen. Just lay off for a while.

504
00:37:39.840 --> 00:37:42.479
<i>I gotta go check on something.</i>

505
00:37:45.080 --> 00:37:47.548
One minute. that's all I'm asking.

506
00:37:47.640 --> 00:37:49.437
One minute to speak to them.

507
00:37:49.520 --> 00:37:51.476
All right. Get back. Get back.

508
00:37:51.560 --> 00:37:53.835
All right. look.

509
00:37:53.920 --> 00:37:57.913
You let me in right now.
or I call the INS. <i>comprende?</i>

510
00:38:00.400 --> 00:38:05.315
This is the last time these kids
are gonna have to speak to their parents.

511
00:38:06.360 --> 00:38:07.429
All right?

512
00:38:07.760 --> 00:38:09.796
All right. Come on. Come on.

513
00:38:19.480 --> 00:38:22.995
What were you doing. Hans?
What were you doing?

514
00:38:37.680 --> 00:38:39.432
<i>(beeping)</i>

515
00:38:44.640 --> 00:38:47.712
Jesus. Mary. mother of God.

516
00:38:51.000 --> 00:38:53.514
Al. listen to me! It's a double-cross!

517
00:38:53.600 --> 00:38:55.158
The roof is wired to...

518
00:38:57.760 --> 00:38:58.749
<i>(Powell) John?</i>

519
00:39:01.040 --> 00:39:02.519
<i>John!</i>

520
00:39:02.840 --> 00:39:04.558
John. come in!

521
00:39:04.640 --> 00:39:08.599
Did you get that?
- Something about a double-cross.

522
00:39:08.680 --> 00:39:10.910
Tell me about it.

523
00:39:16.360 --> 00:39:18.510
We are both professionals.

524
00:39:20.560 --> 00:39:22.152
This is personal.

525
00:39:22.240 --> 00:39:23.389
<i>(radio smashes)</i>

526
00:39:23.480 --> 00:39:24.799
Aww...

527
00:39:44.920 --> 00:39:47.115
They're coming!

528
00:39:47.640 --> 00:39:49.232
Choppers are coming.

529
00:39:49.520 --> 00:39:52.717
Time to gather your flock. Miss Gennero.

530
00:39:52.800 --> 00:39:56.713
<i>(TV) Your mom and dad</i>
<i>are very important people.</i>

531
00:39:56.800 --> 00:39:58.677
<i>They're very brave people.</i>

532
00:39:58.760 --> 00:40:02.594
<i>Is there something you'd like</i>
<i>to say to them. if they're watching?</i>

533
00:40:02.680 --> 00:40:05.717
<i>Come home.</i>

534
00:40:13.840 --> 00:40:15.114
Mrs McClane.

535
00:40:18.240 --> 00:40:21.437
How nice to make your acquaintance.

536
00:40:22.920 --> 00:40:24.433
<i>(screaming)</i>

537
00:40:24.520 --> 00:40:26.431
On your feet. everyone! To the roof!

538
00:40:26.520 --> 00:40:29.080
Lock them up there and come right back.

539
00:40:56.720 --> 00:41:00.952
You should have heard your brother squeal...
when I broke his fucking neck!

540
00:41:04.080 --> 00:41:06.355
What do you figure the breakage?

541
00:41:12.200 --> 00:41:14.509
I can live with that.

542
00:41:14.600 --> 00:41:16.318
Get this thing on the deck.

543
00:41:16.400 --> 00:41:19.312
They're expecting transports. not gunships.

544
00:41:30.840 --> 00:41:32.592
Move it! Come on! Move!

545
00:41:32.680 --> 00:41:34.193
Come on! Come on!

546
00:41:34.280 --> 00:41:35.474
Move it!

547
00:41:36.640 --> 00:41:37.834
Go! Move!

548
00:41:41.560 --> 00:41:42.470
<i>(Hans)</i> Theo.

549
00:41:43.000 --> 00:41:44.513
A little bonus for us.

550
00:41:44.600 --> 00:41:46.511
Please. sit down. Sit down!

551
00:41:46.600 --> 00:41:49.194
A policeman's wife might come in handy.

552
00:41:49.280 --> 00:41:51.669
McClane. I have some news for you.

553
00:41:52.680 --> 00:41:53.908
McClane?

554
00:42:04.920 --> 00:42:06.148
Move!

555
00:42:08.720 --> 00:42:09.436
Come on!

556
00:42:21.760 --> 00:42:23.955
<i>(McClane)</i> Motherfucker! I'll kill you!

557
00:42:27.720 --> 00:42:28.755
Armed.

558
00:42:29.200 --> 00:42:31.156
The truck?
- The truck.

559
00:42:38.040 --> 00:42:41.919
After all your posturing.
all your little speeches...

560
00:42:42.000 --> 00:42:44.275
...you're nothing but a common thief.

561
00:42:44.480 --> 00:42:46.869
I am an exceptional thief. Mrs McClane.

562
00:42:46.960 --> 00:42:51.351
And since I'm moving up to kidnapping.
you should be more polite.

563
00:42:57.280 --> 00:42:59.316
<i>(McClane)</i> You motherfucker!

564
00:42:59.400 --> 00:43:02.710
I'm gonna fuckin' cook you.
and I'm gonna fuckin' eat you!

565
00:43:24.400 --> 00:43:26.391
I don't like this. Sarge.

566
00:43:33.800 --> 00:43:39.477
Yee-hah!
Just like fucking Saigon. eh. Slick?

567
00:43:40.960 --> 00:43:43.713
I was in junior high. dickhead.

568
00:44:10.480 --> 00:44:11.879
Where's Holly?

569
00:44:11.960 --> 00:44:13.359
Where's Holly Gennero?

570
00:44:13.440 --> 00:44:15.476
Holly Gennero? Where's Holly?

571
00:44:15.560 --> 00:44:17.312
Where's Holly? Where is she?

572
00:44:17.400 --> 00:44:18.628
They took her!
- Where?

573
00:44:18.720 --> 00:44:19.709
The vault!

574
00:44:19.800 --> 00:44:21.950
Where is the vault?
- The 30th floor!

575
00:44:22.040 --> 00:44:23.871
They just took her!

576
00:44:24.080 --> 00:44:26.116
Get downstairs!

577
00:44:26.200 --> 00:44:29.237
The whole fucking roof
is wired to blow! Get down!

578
00:44:29.320 --> 00:44:31.788
Get down! Get the fuck downstairs!

579
00:44:33.920 --> 00:44:36.673
They made us. Bureau.
You got a terrorist shooting hostages.

580
00:44:36.760 --> 00:44:38.398
I see him! Break left!

581
00:44:44.400 --> 00:44:45.992
Nail that sucker!

582
00:44:53.800 --> 00:44:56.712
I'm on your side. you assholes!

583
00:44:56.800 --> 00:44:59.792
Swing around again!
I'll bag this little bastard.

584
00:45:17.920 --> 00:45:19.672
What the fuck...

585
00:45:21.560 --> 00:45:24.313
Oh. John. what the fuck are you doing?

586
00:45:24.400 --> 00:45:27.153
How the fuck did you get into this shit?

587
00:45:30.920 --> 00:45:32.433
<i>(screaming)</i>

588
00:45:36.760 --> 00:45:40.036
There's something wrong!
They're coming back down!

589
00:45:40.120 --> 00:45:42.190
Blow the roof.
- But Karl's up there!

590
00:45:42.280 --> 00:45:43.633
Blow the roof!

591
00:45:46.760 --> 00:45:49.513
I promise I will never even think...

592
00:45:49.600 --> 00:45:52.478
...about going up in a tall building again.

593
00:45:55.680 --> 00:45:57.910
Oh. God. please don't let me die!

594
00:47:25.800 --> 00:47:28.189
Holy Christ!

595
00:47:29.320 --> 00:47:31.834
We're gonna need
some more FBI guys. I guess.

596
00:47:41.120 --> 00:47:42.030
<i>(ding)</i>

597
00:47:44.080 --> 00:47:45.798
Jesus fucking Christ!

598
00:47:46.720 --> 00:47:47.789
Fuck!

599
00:47:57.360 --> 00:47:59.157
<i>(clattering)</i>

600
00:48:07.520 --> 00:48:09.351
<i>(engine starts)</i>

601
00:48:11.200 --> 00:48:13.634
What the fuck is going on?

602
00:48:15.440 --> 00:48:20.389
<i>(Holly)</i> What are you gonna do?
Sit here while the building falls down?

603
00:48:20.480 --> 00:48:21.708
<i>(shouting)</i>

604
00:48:26.880 --> 00:48:27.710
Shit!

605
00:48:27.800 --> 00:48:29.597
All right!

606
00:48:31.000 --> 00:48:32.149
Hey! Hey!

607
00:48:33.080 --> 00:48:34.798
Hang on. baby.

608
00:48:34.880 --> 00:48:36.393
Hang on. honey.

609
00:48:37.400 --> 00:48:38.389
Oh. God.

610
00:48:58.560 --> 00:49:00.039
<i>(tyres squeal)</i>

611
00:49:21.680 --> 00:49:23.318
<i>(McClane)</i> Hans!

612
00:49:37.240 --> 00:49:38.912
Jesus.

613
00:49:39.000 --> 00:49:42.117
Hi. honey.

614
00:50:02.320 --> 00:50:06.108
So that's what this was all about?
A fuckin' robbery?

615
00:50:06.560 --> 00:50:07.709
Put down the gun.

616
00:50:09.360 --> 00:50:11.555
Why'd you have to nuke the whole building?

617
00:50:11.640 --> 00:50:14.552
Well. when you steal $600.
you can just disappear.

618
00:50:14.640 --> 00:50:17.518
When you steal 600 million.
they will find you...

619
00:50:17.600 --> 00:50:19.795
...unless they think you're already dead.

620
00:50:19.880 --> 00:50:21.916
Put down the gun.

621
00:50:29.040 --> 00:50:29.916
<i>(Holly gasps)</i>

622
00:50:31.960 --> 00:50:33.552
<i>(Hans) Nein.</i> This is mine.

623
00:50:36.680 --> 00:50:38.432
You got me.

624
00:50:38.520 --> 00:50:41.193
Still the cowboy. Mr McClane.

625
00:50:41.280 --> 00:50:42.872
Americans... all alike.

626
00:50:42.960 --> 00:50:46.748
This time. John Wayne does not walk off
into the sunset with Grace Kelly.

627
00:50:46.840 --> 00:50:48.592
That was Gary Cooper. asshole.

628
00:50:48.680 --> 00:50:50.398
Enough jokes.

629
00:50:50.480 --> 00:50:53.233
You'd have made a pretty
good cowboy yourself. Hans.

630
00:50:53.320 --> 00:50:57.791
<i>(Hans)</i> Oh. yes. What was it
you said to me before?

631
00:50:57.880 --> 00:51:01.475
Yippee-ki-yay. motherfucker.

632
00:51:01.560 --> 00:51:02.879
<i>(laughing)</i>

633
00:51:21.760 --> 00:51:22.749
Holly!

634
00:51:28.080 --> 00:51:29.513
Happy trails. Hans.

635
00:51:34.800 --> 00:51:36.358
Aah!

636
00:51:36.440 --> 00:51:38.192
<i>(Holly screaming)</i>

637
00:52:12.360 --> 00:52:14.157
I hope that's not a hostage.

638
00:52:37.680 --> 00:52:39.750
<i>(sirens)</i>

639
00:52:41.400 --> 00:52:45.234
Gimme water hook-ups
for engine companies 5. 3. 9. 6.

640
00:52:48.760 --> 00:52:50.751
Over here. It's a better angle.

641
00:52:52.320 --> 00:52:53.548
<i>(horn honks)</i>

642
00:52:54.800 --> 00:52:57.712
Keep it going. now. Keep it going.

643
00:53:02.560 --> 00:53:06.030
Come on. We're going to miss it!
- OK. Hand me my notes!

644
00:53:28.120 --> 00:53:32.033
What was it like in there?
How did they treat you?

645
00:54:16.360 --> 00:54:18.032
Al. this is my wife Holly.

646
00:54:18.120 --> 00:54:19.951
Holly Gennero.

647
00:54:20.680 --> 00:54:22.352
Holly McClane.

648
00:54:22.440 --> 00:54:24.032
Hello. Holly.

649
00:54:24.120 --> 00:54:25.997
You got yourself a good man.

650
00:54:26.080 --> 00:54:27.991
You take good care of him.

651
00:54:28.640 --> 00:54:30.073
<i>(Robinson)</i> McClane!

652
00:54:30.280 --> 00:54:32.748
McClane. I want a debriefing!

653
00:54:32.840 --> 00:54:35.400
You got some things to answer for. mister.

654
00:54:35.480 --> 00:54:37.152
Ellis' murder. for one thing.

655
00:54:37.240 --> 00:54:40.835
Property damage.
interfering with police business.

656
00:54:40.960 --> 00:54:42.439
<i>(screaming)</i>

657
00:55:19.560 --> 00:55:22.518
<i>(Robinson)</i> Go inside.
see if there's anybody else!

658
00:55:32.840 --> 00:55:35.308
No. This one's with me.

659
00:55:42.960 --> 00:55:44.234
<i>(horn honks)</i>

660
00:55:44.840 --> 00:55:46.398
Mr McClane. Mr McClane!

661
00:55:46.480 --> 00:55:51.315
Now that it's all over and after this
incredible ordeal. what are your feelings?

662
00:55:52.840 --> 00:55:54.751
<i>(laughter)</i>

663
00:55:55.920 --> 00:55:57.273
Well. well. well.

664
00:55:57.360 --> 00:56:01.433
Merry Christmas. Argyle.
- Merry Christmas.

665
00:56:04.840 --> 00:56:05.829
<i>Did you get that?</i>

666
00:56:08.320 --> 00:56:11.710
If this is their idea of Christmas.
I gotta be here for New Year's.

667
00:56:17.320 --> 00:56:20.710
<i>(Vaughn Monroe singing)</i>
<i>Oh. the weather outside is frightful</i>

668
00:56:20.800 --> 00:56:23.633
<i>But the fire is so delightful</i>

669
00:56:24.520 --> 00:56:27.751
<i>And since we've no place to go</i>

670
00:56:27.840 --> 00:56:31.150
<i>Let it snow. let it snow. let it snow.</i>

671
00:56:32.040 --> 00:56:34.918
<i>It doesn't show signs of stopping</i>

672
00:56:35.000 --> 00:56:38.436
<i>And I brought some corn for popping</i>

673
00:56:38.960 --> 00:56:42.191
<i>The lights are turned way down low</i>

674
00:56:42.280 --> 00:56:45.716
<i>Let it snow. let it snow. let it snow</i>

675
00:56:46.160 --> 00:56:49.391
<i>When we finally kiss goodnight</i>

676
00:56:49.480 --> 00:56:53.029
<i>How I hate goin' out in the storm</i>

677
00:56:53.480 --> 00:56:57.393
<i>But if you really hold me tight</i>

678
00:56:57.480 --> 00:57:00.199
<i>All the way home. I'll be warm</i>

679
00:57:00.800 --> 00:57:04.031
<i>The fire is slowly dying</i>

680
00:57:04.120 --> 00:57:07.476
<i>And. my dear. we're still good-byeing</i>

681
00:57:07.920 --> 00:57:11.071
<i>But as long as you love me so</i>

682
00:57:11.160 --> 00:57:13.435
<i>Let it snow</i>

683
00:57:13.520 --> 00:57:15.272
<i>Let it snow</i>

684
00:57:15.360 --> 00:57:19.956
<i>Let it snow</i>

685
00:57:25.080 --> 00:57:28.516
<i>(choir singing Beethoven's</i>
<i>"Ode to Joy" in German)</i>

686
01:00:34.800 --> 01:00:36.950
Subtitles by Visiontext

687
01:01:06.560 --> 01:01:08.551
